div.note:
MS rica e amant;
                    apparent scribal error, cf. Macario,Ancora per moi sera rico e manent," ll. 14756, 14762;
                        mant = "manant", syncopated typical in Franco-Italian.

coda, lenition;
                    the image is of wolves following closely behind the tail of the she wolf in
                    heat.

MS n?n;
                    scribal correction with o written above indisctinct
                    middle letter.

MS liois;
                    scribe attempts to correct this word by adding an i
                    after the initial l and making the second i an r.

Carlo Magno;
                    this is the only mention of Charlemagne's full name in the text. It occures once
                    in T and twice in B.

MS gnanda;
                    scribal error with ondulating titulus over n to correct
                    to r.

MS curera;
                    scribal correction with ve written in
                    superscript.

MS contesse;
                    scribe attempts to correct last e then blots out and
                    writes a above.

MS elesalvais;
                    probably an unintentional repetition of the previous e
                        lle.

MS dromento;
                    this correction suggests that the scribe attempts to normalize his language,
                    avoiding the voicing of predental plosives.

MS çascun à;
                    scribe omits omo then adds it later in
                    superscript.

MS cher;
                    proposed emendation based on forms in ll. 4201 and 4315; Br Tu
                        croi q'i leçent; T Tu credy.

MS star a;
                    scribal correction, in pié
                    written in superscript

MS ...in;
                    manuscript damged here; Sandin is clear from context and
                    visible final -in.
